 their bodies? Why has it become a trend? Na hunger dey cause am. You really cannot blame them, all na hustle”. Vanguard News Nigeria Popular Nollywood actress, Maryam Charles has shared her opinion about the recent suspension of Chief Justice of Nigeria, Walter Onnoghen, by President Muhammadu Buhari, over his alleged failure to declare his personal assets before taking office in 2017. January 27, 2019 In "Entertainment" With internet fraud on the rise, Nollywood screen diva, Maryam Charles, has revealed why some engage in the shameful act . Maryam said, laziness of the mind, body and spirit is the reason why many engage in fraud - She also asked them to try telling the truth for a… November 1, 2017 In "News" Former first lady of Nigeria, Mrs. Maryam Babangida (nee Okogwu) was born a Christian. She was then known as Maria. She converted to Islam following her marriage to General Ibrahim Babangida. The duo reportedly met in Kaduna. December 28, 2009 In "News"